{% comment %}
  Ascend Performance Nutrition — ROOKIE Tier MasterClass
  Tier: Rookie (Score 0-40)
  Personalization: ?score= ?name= ?gap1= ?gap2= ?gap3=
  Version: 1.0 | Production Ready
{% endcomment %}

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Barlow:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<section id="apn-masterclass-tier-rookie" style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif; background:#F4F4F2; color:#333333;">

<style>
  #apn-masterclass-tier-rookie * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  /* ---- TOKENS ---- */
  #apn-masterclass-tier-rookie {
    --teal:       #108474;
    --tier-green: #22C55E;
    --black:      #0D0D0D;
    --body:       #333333;
    --bg:         #F4F4F2;
    --bg2:        #F8F8F8;
    --border:     #E2E8F0;
    --warning:    #F59E0B;
    --warn-bg:    #FFFBEB;
    --font:       'Barlow', sans-serif;
  }

  /* ---- GLOBAL ---- */
  .apn-r-wrap { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
  .apn-r-wrap--wide { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }

  .apn-r-section-label {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    display: block;
  }

  .apn-r-divider {
    width: 64px;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--teal);
    margin: 20px 0 32px 0;
  }
  .apn-r-divider--center { margin: 20px auto 32px auto; }

  .apn-r-h1 {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: clamp(38px, 6vw, 54px);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.08;
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  .apn-r-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 36px);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .apn-r-h3 {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 20px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .apn-r-body {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  .apn-r-body + .apn-r-body { margin-top: 16px; }

  /* ---- MODULE SPACING ---- */
  .apn-r-module { padding: 80px 0; }
  .apn-r-module--dark { background: var(--black); }
  .apn-r-module--bg2 { background: var(--bg2); }
  .apn-r-module--bg { background: var(--bg); }

  /* ---- HERO ---- */
  .apn-r-hero {
    background: var(--black);
    padding: 100px 0 80px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .apn-r-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--teal);
  }
  .apn-r-hero-eyebrow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .apn-r-tier-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--tier-green);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .apn-r-hero-welcome {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .apn-r-hero-welcome strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); }
  .apn-r-hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    margin-top: 24px;
    max-width: 600px;
  }
  .apn-r-module-list {
    margin-top: 40px;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .apn-r-module-list li {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .apn-r-module-list li::before {
    content: '';
    display: inline-block;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--teal);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .apn-r-module-list .read-time {
    margin-left: auto;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }
  .apn-r-scroll-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 44px;
    padding: 14px 32px;
    background: var(--teal);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 60px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }
  .apn-r-scroll-btn:hover { opacity: 0.88; }

  /* ---- PULL QUOTE ---- */
  .apn-r-pullquote {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);
    background: var(--bg2);
    padding: 24px 28px;
    margin: 40px 0;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
  .apn-r-pullquote p {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
  }
  .apn-r-pullquote cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
  }

  /* ---- ASSIGNMENT BLOCK ---- */
  .apn-r-assignment {
    border-top: 3px solid var(--teal);
    background: #F4F4F2;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    margin-top: 28px;
    border-radius: 0 0 4px 4px;
  }
  .apn-r-assignment .assignment-label {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    display: block;
  }
  .apn-r-assignment p {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
  }
  .apn-r-assignment ul {
    margin-top: 10px;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .apn-r-assignment ul li {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  /* ---- SCRIPTURE ---- */
  .apn-r-scripture {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 40px 32px;
    margin: 48px 0;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .apn-r-scripture p {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--body);
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .apn-r-scripture cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
  }

  /* ---- WARNING CALLOUT ---- */
  .apn-r-warning {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--warning);
    background: var(--warn-bg);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin: 32px 0;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
  .apn-r-warning .warn-label {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--warning);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    display: block;
  }
  .apn-r-warning p {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #92400E;
  }

  /* ---- DATA CALLOUT ---- */
  .apn-r-data-callout {
    background: var(--black);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin: 32px 0;
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .apn-r-data-callout .stat {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 36px;
    color: var(--teal);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    min-width: 80px;
  }
  .apn-r-data-callout .stat-body { flex: 1; }
  .apn-r-data-callout .stat-body strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .apn-r-data-callout .stat-body span {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* ---- GAP CARDS ---- */
  .apn-r-gap-card {
    background: #fff;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }
  .apn-r-gap-card .gap-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .apn-r-gap-card .gap-name {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--black);
    text-transform: capitalize;
  }
  .apn-r-gap-card .gap-urgency {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .gap-urgency--critical { background: #FEE2E2; color: #991B1B; }
  .gap-urgency--moderate { background: #FEF3C7; color: #92400E; }
  .gap-urgency--manageable { background: #D1FAE5; color: #065F46; }
  .apn-r-gap-card p {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .apn-r-gap-card a {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--teal);
    text-decoration: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .apn-r-gap-card a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* ---- PRODUCT CARD ---- */
  .apn-r-product-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 32px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .apn-r-product-card .prod-top {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .apn-r-product-card .prod-name {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--black);
  }
  .apn-r-product-card .prod-price {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--teal);
  }
  .apn-r-product-card .prod-mechanism {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    display: block;
  }
  .apn-r-product-card p {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .apn-r-product-card .prod-protocol {
    background: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--body);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .apn-r-product-card .prod-protocol strong {
    color: var(--black);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* ---- WEEK BLOCK ---- */
  .apn-r-week {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: #fff;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .apn-r-week-header {
    background: var(--black);
    padding: 16px 24px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .apn-r-week-header .week-label {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
  }
  .apn-r-week-header .week-title {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .apn-r-week-body { padding: 24px; }
  .apn-r-week-body ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .apn-r-week-body ul li {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
    padding-left: 20px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .apn-r-week-body ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--teal);
  }

  /* ---- TIER PROGRESS ---- */
  .apn-r-tier-progress {
    background: var(--black);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 32px 28px;
    margin: 40px 0;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .apn-r-tier-progress .tier-progress-label {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    display: block;
  }
  .apn-r-tier-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    margin: 20px 0 28px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .tier-bar-item {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
    position: relative;
    min-width: 80px;
  }
  .tier-bar-dot {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin: 0 auto 8px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
  }
  .tier-bar-dot--active { background: var(--tier-green); }
  .tier-bar-name {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
  }
  .tier-bar-name--active { color: var(--tier-green); }
  .tier-bar-line {
    flex: 1;
    height: 2px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    min-width: 20px;
    max-width: 60px;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }

  /* ---- CHALLENGE HABITS ---- */
  .apn-r-habit {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 20px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }
  .apn-r-habit:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .habit-num {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 28px;
    color: var(--teal);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 40px;
  }
  .habit-content strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .habit-content p {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
  }

  /* ---- NEXT STEPS CARDS ---- */
  .apn-r-next-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 24px;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .apn-r-next-card:hover { box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .apn-r-next-card .next-card-label {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    display: block;
  }
  .apn-r-next-card .next-card-title {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    text-transform: capitalize;
  }
  .apn-r-next-card .next-card-desc {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--body);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* ---- CTA BUTTONS ---- */
  .apn-r-cta-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; margin-top: 40px; }
  .apn-r-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 16px 32px;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 60px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: 2px solid transparent;
  }
  .apn-r-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }
  .apn-r-btn--teal { background: var(--teal); color: #fff; border-color: var(--teal); }
  .apn-r-btn--black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; border-color: var(--black); }
  .apn-r-btn--outline { background: transparent; color: #fff; border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); }

  /* ---- DISCOUNT BANNER ---- */
  .apn-r-discount-banner {
    background: var(--teal);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 16px 24px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin: 28px 0;
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .apn-r-discount-banner .code {
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 17px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    padding: 2px 10px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    margin: 0 4px;
  }

  /* ---- FOOTER ---- */
  .apn-r-footer {
    background: var(--black);
    padding: 60px 0 40px;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--teal);
  }
  .apn-r-footer-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .apn-r-footer-signoff {
    font-family: var(--font);
    font-size: 15px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .apn-r-footer-signoff strong {
    display: block;
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  /* ---- RESPONSIVE ---- */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .apn-r-module { padding: 56px 0; }
    .apn-r-hero { padding: 72px 0 60px; }
    .apn-r-data-callout { flex-direction: column; }
    .apn-r-cta-block { align-items: stretch; }
    .apn-r-tier-bar { gap: 4px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- ===================== MODULE 0: HERO ===================== -->
<div class="apn-r-hero">
  <div class="apn-r-wrap">
    <div class="apn-r-hero-eyebrow">
      <span class="apn-r-section-label" style="margin-bottom:0;">Rookie MasterClass</span>
      <span class="apn-r-tier-badge">Rookie Tier</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="apn-r-h1">Your Rookie<br>Performance Profile.</h1>
    <div class="apn-r-divider"></div>

    <p class="apn-r-hero-welcome" id="apn-r-welcome-line">
      Welcome back. Your overall score: loading...
    </p>

    <p class="apn-r-hero-sub">
      This page translates your quiz results into a clear performance picture. You will learn what your Rookie score means in concrete behavioral terms, where your biggest gains are hiding, and the exact 4-week framework to start moving up.
    </p>

    <ul class="apn-r-module-list">
      <li>Module 1: What Your Score Means <span class="read-time">2 min</span></li>
      <li>Module 2: The Rookie Performance Profile <span class="read-time">5 min</span></li>
      <li>Module 3: Your Gap Snapshot <span class="read-time">5 min</span></li>
      <li>Module 4: The Rookie Priority Framework <span class="read-time">10 min</span></li>
      <li>Module 5: The Rookie Foundation Stack <span class="read-time">5 min</span></li>
      <li>Module 6: Your Rookie Challenge <span class="read-time">3 min</span></li>
      <li>Module 7: Next Steps <span class="read-time">3 min</span></li>
    </ul>

    <button class="apn-r-scroll-btn" onclick="document.getElementById('apn-r-module1').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})">
      Start MasterClass
    </button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ===================== MODULE 1: WHAT YOUR SCORE MEANS ===================== -->
<div class="apn-r-module apn-r-module--bg" id="apn-r-module1">
  <div class="apn-r-wrap">
    <span class="apn-r-section-label">Your Tier Report</span>
    <h2 class="apn-r-h2">What Your Score Actually Means.</h2>
    <div class="apn-r-divider"></div>

    <p class="apn-r-body">
      A Rookie score (0 to 40) is not a judgment. It is a measurement. It tells you something precise: your performance foundation has significant gaps across multiple pillars simultaneously. That is not unusual for athletes who train hard but have not yet built a system around their training. The score measures behavior, not effort. You can be working hard and still score in this range.
    </p>

    <div class="apn-r-data-callout" style="margin-top:32px;">
      <div class="stat" id="apn-r-score-display">--</div>
      <div class="stat-body">
        <strong>Your Overall Score</strong>
        <span>Rookie tier: 0 to 40. This range means multiple pillars (sleep, nutrition, recovery, training structure) are operating below baseline performance thresholds at the same time.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="apn-r-h3" style="margin-top:40px;">What defines the Rookie tier in observable terms.</h3>
    <p class="apn-r-body">
      Rookie-tier athletes share four consistent behaviors, regardless of sport. Sleep averages below 7 hours per night with no consistent wake time. Protein intake falls below 0.7 grams per pound of bodyweight, which means the leucine threshold required to trigger muscle protein synthesis is not being hit consistently. There is no structured training program in place, so adaptive stress is inconsistent. And there is no supplement foundation: no creatine, no post-training protein protocol, no recovery structure.
    </p>
    <p class="apn-r-body">
      None of these are permanent. Every one of them is fixable in 30 days with the right order of operations.
    </p>

    <h3 class="apn-r-h3" style="margin-top:36px;">The gap between Rookie and the next tier up.</h3>
    <p class="apn-r-body">
      Athlete-tier athletes (score 41 to 65) have one thing Rookies do not: a system. They do not necessarily sleep more by accident or eat more protein by willpower alone. They have a protocol for it. Sleep is protected by a consistent schedule. Protein is planned around meals. Training follows a program. The behavioral gap between Rookie and Athlete is not talent or genetics. It is the presence or absence of a repeatable system.
    </p>

    <div class="apn-r-warning">
      <span class="warn-label">Where Most Rookie Athletes Get Stuck</span>
      <p>The most common pattern at this tier: information overload combined with zero execution. The Rookie athlete has researched supplements, watched training videos, and knows the principles. But nothing is locked in as habit. The week is reactive. Training happens when motivated. Eating is by feel. Sleep is what is left after everything else. The knowledge exists. The architecture does not.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="apn-r-h3" style="margin-top:36px;">One insight you can use today.</h3>
    <p class="apn-r-body">
      Set a wake time. Pick a time between 5:30 AM and 7:00 AM and commit to it every day this week, including weekends. Do nothing else differently yet. Research on circadian rhythm consistency shows that a fixed wake time anchors the full sleep architecture more effectively than targeting total sleep hours alone. It is the single lowest-effort, highest-return change available at this tier. Set the alarm tonight.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ===================== MODULE 2: THE ROOKIE PERFORMANCE PROFILE ===================== -->
<div class="apn-r-module apn-r-module--bg2" id="apn-r-module2">
  <div class="apn-r-wrap">
    <span class="apn-r-section-label">Your Performance Profile</span>
    <h2 class="apn-r-h2">The Rookie Performance Profile.</h2>
    <div class="apn-r-divider"></div>

    <p class="apn-r-body">
      Every tier has a behavioral fingerprint. Here is what Rookie-tier performance looks like in the real world, and what separates it from the next level.
    </p>

    <div style="margin-top:40px; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:24px;">

      <div class="apn-r-product-card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--tier-green); border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: none; border: none; border-left: 4px solid var(--tier-green); background: #fff; border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; padding: 24px 28px;">
        <span class="prod-mechanism">Behavior 01</span>
        <div class="apn-r-h3" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Inconsistency is the ceiling.</div>
        <p class="apn-r-body">Training, sleep, and nutrition all fluctuate significantly from week to week. Some weeks are great. Some are not. The problem is not the bad weeks. It is the absence of a floor. Without a consistent minimum, the body cannot build on top of previous adaptation. Research on training adaptation shows that the minimum effective dose applied consistently outperforms high-volume training applied sporadically. Inconsistency is not a motivation problem. It is a systems problem.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="apn-r-product-card" style="border: none; border-left: 4px solid var(--tier-green); background: #fff; border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; padding: 24px 28px;">
        <span class="prod-mechanism">Behavior 02</span>
        <div class="apn-r-h3" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Decisions made by feel, not protocol.</div>
        <p class="apn-r-body">What to eat, when to train, how long to sleep. All of it decided in the moment based on how the athlete feels. This is fine when feeling is good. It fails when life gets busy, when motivation dips, or when stress increases. Protocol removes the decision. When the decision is already made, execution becomes the only variable. Athlete-tier athletes do not rely on feeling motivated. They rely on their protocol.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="apn-r-product-card" style="border: none; border-left: 4px solid var(--tier-green); background: #fff; border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; padding: 24px 28px;">
        <span class="prod-mechanism">Behavior 03</span>
        <div class="apn-r-h3" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Knows too much. Executes too little.</div>
        <p class="apn-r-body">The Rookie athlete has absorbed a significant amount of performance information. Protein targets, sleep hygiene principles, creatine loading, periodization concepts. But the gap between knowledge and execution is large. Adding more information does not close this gap. Adding fewer, simpler commitments does. The brain executes on habits, not on knowledge. The priority at this tier is reducing the list to one thing and locking it in before adding the next.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="apn-r-warning" style="margin-top:40px;">
      <span class="warn-label">The Most Common Rookie Mistake</span>
      <p>Trying to change everything at once. A new training program, a new diet plan, three new supplements, and a recovery protocol all starting in the same week. None of it sticks. Habit formation research is clear: willpower is a finite resource, and stacking too many behavioral changes simultaneously depletes it before any single change becomes automatic. The Rookie who tries to fix everything in Week 1 is back to zero by Week 3.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="apn-r-pullquote" style="margin-top:40px;">
      <p>"Coaches working with Rookie-tier athletes consistently report the same pattern: athletes with significant physical potential who plateau early because they have no system. The ones who break out fastest are not the most gifted. They are the ones who commit to one protocol and execute it without exception until it is automatic."</p>
      <cite>Performance Coaching Observation, Ascend Athlete Data</cite>
    </div>

    <h3 class="apn-r-h3" style="margin-top:40px;">The compounding opportunity.</h3>
    <p class="apn-r-body">
      This is the most important thing to understand about the Rookie tier: you are at the highest leverage point available. When the baseline is low, fixing one pillar delivers outsized results because the systems are interconnected. Fixing sleep first is not just about sleep. Consistent 7 to 8 hour sleep improves insulin sensitivity, which improves nutrient partitioning, which means the protein you eat does more. Better sleep also reduces cortisol chronically, which accelerates recovery between sessions, which means your training produces more adaptation. One change. Multiple returns. This is the compounding opportunity that only exists at this tier.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

