<!-- ===================== MODULE 6: THE ROOKIE CHALLENGE ===================== -->
<div class="apn-r-module apn-r-module--dark" id="apn-r-module6">
  <div class="apn-r-wrap">
    <span class="apn-r-section-label" style="color: var(--teal);">The Commitment</span>
    <h2 class="apn-r-h2" style="color:#fff;">Your Rookie Challenge.</h2>
    <div class="apn-r-divider"></div>

    <p class="apn-r-body" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">
      Four habits. Specific. Measurable. Non-negotiable for 30 days. This is how you move from Rookie to Athlete. Not inspiration. Not ambition. Four locked-in behaviors executed daily.
    </p>

    <div style="margin-top:40px;">
      <div class="apn-r-habit">
        <div class="habit-num">01</div>
        <div class="habit-content">
          <strong>Hit your wake time within 30 minutes, every day.</strong>
          <p>Including weekends. Non-negotiable. A consistent wake time is the single anchor of your entire sleep architecture. Miss this and you undermine everything downstream. Success measure: 6 of 7 days per week for 4 consecutive weeks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="apn-r-habit">
        <div class="habit-num">02</div>
        <div class="habit-content">
          <strong>Hit your protein target 5 of 7 days every week.</strong>
          <p>Calculate it (bodyweight x 0.7g minimum), plan for it, track it. Not as a punishment. As a data point. Five of seven days is the minimum threshold for measurable adaptation in lean mass over a 30-day block. Below that, you are leaving recovery and growth on the floor.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="apn-r-habit">
        <div class="habit-num">03</div>
        <div class="habit-content">
          <strong>Take 5g creatine every single day for 30 days.</strong>
          <p>Daily. No exceptions. Phosphocreatine saturation requires consistent intake. Missing 2 to 3 days per week eliminates the benefit. Set a daily alarm. This is the most important habit to automate because it requires the least effort once it is a reflex.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="apn-r-habit">
        <div class="habit-num">04</div>
        <div class="habit-content">
          <strong>Log every training session for 30 days.</strong>
          <p>Exercise, sets, reps, weight. In a notebook or your phone. This creates the data you need to confirm progressive overload is occurring. Athletes who log consistently progress 40% faster on compound lifts over a 12-week period compared to athletes who train without records, because they eliminate the guessing about whether weight increased or volume progressed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="apn-r-pullquote" style="margin-top:48px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border-left-color: var(--teal);">
      <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);">"Every elite athlete was a Rookie. The difference between who stays there and who does not is not talent. It is the decision to stop winging it and start building one thing at a time."</p>
      <cite>Sutton Huggins, Founder and CEO, Ascend Performance Nutrition</cite>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:48px; padding: 32px; background: rgba(16,132,116,0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(16,132,116,0.3); border-radius: 6px;">
      <span class="apn-r-section-label">What Separates Athletes Who Level Up</span>
      <p class="apn-r-body" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8); margin-bottom:16px;">
        The Rookie athletes who reach Athlete tier within 60 days share one consistent pattern: they do not try to do everything. They choose four habits. They execute them with monotonous consistency. They do not add a fifth habit until the fourth is automatic. They retake the quiz after 30 days and let the data tell them what changed.
      </p>
      <p class="apn-r-body" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8);">
